Before running the application, you have to:
- install Ruby (1.8.6+), Rails (2.0+), Rake, RubyGems
- create an empty database (MySQL or SQLite)
- make sure you have access to a SMTP server (for sending password reminder emails)
- create a file "config/database.yml" using the template file "config/database.yml.example" and fill in with your
  database connection parameters
- create a file "config/initializers/local_config.rb" using the template file "config/initializers/local_config.rb.example"
  and enter your SMTP server settings
- if you used GMail or Google Apps email in the file above, uncomment the two lines below "tls support for gmail" and
  install "tlsmail" gem
- migrate the database ("rake db:migrate")
